Back up all data on your Chromebook, as this process will wipe the storage.

Create a recovery USB drive for ChromeOS, just in case you need to restore it later.

DEVOLPER MODE

Enable Developer Mode on your Chromebook:

Turn off the device.

Press Esc + Refresh + Power to enter recovery mode.

Choose "Turn OS Verification Off" and proceed.

Replace the Chromebook's firmware with Coreboot or a custom firmware like MrChromebox firmware:

Follow detailed instructions from MrChromebox's website.

Install the firmware update via USB.
